    <h2>Interactions to Be Aware Of</h2>
    <p>These mushrooms generally do NOT cancel each other out — but here are the specific situations requiring care.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="caution-list">
    <div class="caution-card">
      <div class="caution-title">Amanita muscaria + Any other mushroom in this list</div>
      <p class="caution-desc">Amanita works through GABA-A receptors (CNS depressant pathway) — completely different from the beta-glucan immune pathways all other mushrooms use. Combining it with Reishi (calming) or Cordyceps (stimulating) could create unpredictable CNS effects. Should NOT be casually stacked without professional guidance.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="caution-card">
      <div class="caution-title">Maitake + Blood sugar medications (Metformin, insulin)</div>
      <p class="caution-desc">Maitake independently lowers blood glucose. Combined with diabetes medications, blood sugar can drop dangerously low. Not a mushroom-to-mushroom conflict — it's a medication interaction. Monitor closely and discuss with a doctor.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="caution-card">
      <div class="caution-title">Cordyceps or Maitake + Blood thinners (Warfarin, etc.)</div>
      <p class="caution-desc">Both Cordyceps and Maitake have blood-thinning properties. Combined with Warfarin or other anticoagulants, this could significantly increase bleeding risk. Discuss with your healthcare provider before use.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="caution-card">
      <div class="caution-title">Multiple immune-boosters + autoimmune conditions</div>
      <p class="caution-desc">Turkey Tail, Reishi, Maitake, Chaga, and Cordyceps all modulate the immune system — great for healthy people. However, those with autoimmune conditions (lupus, RA, MS) should be cautious stacking several immune-boosters, as overstimulating an already overactive immune system can worsen symptoms.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
</section>

